Provided, furthermore,

That loanable funds channeled as compliance under this subsection shall not be counted as compliance under subsections (b), (c), (d), (e) and (f) even if said funds are later used by conduit banks in activities similar to those provided for in subsections (b), (c), (d), (e) and (f);

Rediscount with the universal banks and commercial banks, including local branches of foreign banks eligible paper covering agriculture, fisheries and agrarian reform credits, including loans covered by guarantees of the QUEDANCOR, and the PCIC:

Provided,

That re discounted paper shall no longer be eligible as compliance on the part of the originating bank;

Lend for the construction and upgrading of infrastructure including, but not limited to, farm-to-market roads, as well as the provision of post harvest facilities and other public infrastructure that will benefit the agriculture, fisheries and agrarian reform sector;
